laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is fluid-filled, measuring up to 0.8 cm. A relatively hyperdense area is seen at the appendiceal base, which represents focal hyperemia. There is focal wall thickening up to 3 mm. There is mild thickening of the cecum at the base of the appendix with mild mesenteric stranding. No focal fluid collections or free intraperitoneal air.
